@ Ocean

To get it out of the way quickly, I do not think brawl needed a nerf, the card is already an expensive power that has no impact the turn you play it, and requires synergies to really start performing well. With that being said, this is a solid part of hermit's scaling damage package, I often pick it up in Hexaghost acts to get some scaling going, but I usually don't take it until I have the synergies for it in place. it pairs really well with vulnerable from memento, glare and wide open, helps snapshot create more block, and can be a very strong damage multiplier with horror. The most important thing is having some combination of multihit attacks and cheap attacks to use the bruise multiple times in one turn (spray and pray, spite, called shot, enervate, showdown, dead or alive). Even more importantly, having some way to offset the high cost of the card lets you get it in play without being punished too hard, so the 4th energy, mummified hand, boat relics, and snecko eye all help it out a lot. Even with the nerf, this is still a very effective part of hermit's damage scaling package, but I do think that having the right cards/relics before taking it becomes even more important
